# Copilot Studio Agent Config (Manual Auth Only)

This file documents only the exact proven path used in this repository:

- Manual authentication
- Microsoft Entra ID v2 federated credentials
- SharePoint grounding with delegated user access
- Internal and B2B guest users

## Reference Configuration

```json
{
  "agent": {
    "name": "B2B SharePoint Knowledge Agent",
    "description": "Copilot Studio agent with SharePoint grounding for internal and guest users"
  },
  "authentication": {
    "mode": "manual",
    "provider": "microsoft-entra-id-v2-federated-credentials",
    "requireSignIn": true,
    "scopes": [
      "profile",
      "openid"
    ],
    "federatedCredential": {
      "issuer": "<copilot-studio-issuer-value>",
      "subject": "<copilot-studio-subject-value>"
    },
    "appRegistration": {
      "tenantType": "single-tenant",
      "clientId": "<entra-app-client-id>",
      "redirectUri": "https://token.botframework.com/.auth/web/redirect"
    },
    "graphDelegatedPermissions": [
      "openid",
      "profile",
      "User.Read",
      "Sites.Read.All",
      "Files.Read.All"
    ],
    "adminConsentRequired": true
  },
  "knowledgeSource": {
    "type": "sharepoint",
    "siteUrl": "https://your-tenant.sharepoint.com/sites/your-site",
    "accessModel": "delegated-user-context"
  },
  "sharing": {
    "shareFromCopilotStudio": true,
    "allowedUsers": [
      "internal-users",
      "guest-users",
      "or-security-group"
    ]
  },
  "webChannel": {
    "enabled": true,
    "embed": "<iframe src=\"your-copilot-url\"></iframe>"
  }
}
```

## Notes

- This is a documentation reference, not an importable Copilot Studio schema.
- SSO is intentionally not included for this scenario.
- SharePoint access is enforced at runtime based on each user's permissions.
